cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.GT, cs.SOC, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper examines the emergence of governance regimes in self-governing online communities, which can be seen as social networks. 
- cs.CY (Computational Complexity) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of governance regimes and how it affects the fitness of communities. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is another possible category as the paper analyzes the strategies and rules used by communities to manage resource constraints, which can be seen as a game-theoretic problem. 
- cs.SOC (Computational Social Science) is also a possible category as the paper examines the behavior of self-governing communities and how they respond to selection pressures. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper may discuss the algorithms and data structures used by communities to manage their governance systems.
